\f1\b0 \cf3 15\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0After this the word of Jehovah came to Abram in a vision, saying: \'93Do not fear, Abram. I am a shield for you. Your reward will be very great.\'94 \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Abram replied: \'93Sovereign Lord Jehovah, what will you give me, seeing that I continue childless and the one who will inherit my house is a man of Damascus, Eliezer?\'94 \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0Abram added: \'93You have given me no offspring, and a member of my household is succeeding me as heir.\'94 \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0But look! Jehovah\'92s word in reply to him was, \'93This man will not succeed you as heir, but your own son will succeed you as heir.\'94\
\cf4 5\cf5 \'a0He now brought him outside and said: \'93Look up, please, to the heavens and count the stars, if you are able to do so.\'94 Then he said to him: \'93So your offspring will become.\'94 \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0And he put faith in Jehovah, and He counted it to him as righteousness. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0Then he added: \'93I am Jehovah, who brought you out of Ur of the Chaldeans to give you this land as your possession.\'94 \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0To this he said: \'93Sovereign Lord Jehovah, how will I know that I will take possession of it?\'94 \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0He replied to him: \'93Take for me a three\cf7  year \cf5 old heifer, a three\cf7  year \cf5 old female goat, a three\cf7  year \cf5 old ram, a turtledove, and a young pigeon.\'94 \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0So he took all of these and cut them in two and put each part opposite the other, but he did not cut up the birds. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Then the birds of prey began to descend on the carcasses, but Abram kept driving them away.\
\cf4 12\cf5 \'a0When the sun was about to set, a deep sleep fell upon Abram and a great and frightening darkness descended on him. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Then He said to Abram: \'93Know for certain that your offspring will be foreigners in a land not theirs and that the people there will enslave them and afflict them for 400 years. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0But I will judge the nation they will serve, and after that they will go out with many goods. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0As for you, you will go to your forefathers in peace; you will be buried at a good old age. \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0But they will return here in the fourth generation, because the error of the Amorites has not yet reached its full measure.\'94\
\cf4 17\cf5 \'a0When the sun had set and it had become very dark, a smoking furnace appeared, and a fiery torch passed between the pieces. \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0On that day Jehovah made with Abram a covenant, saying: \'93To your offspring I will give this land, from the river of Egypt to the great river, the river Euphrates: \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0the land of the Kenites, the Kenizzites, the Kadmonites, \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim, \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

