\f1\b0 \cf3 16\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Now Abram\'92s wife Sarai had borne him no children, but she had an Egyptian servant whose name was Hagar. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0So Sarai said to Abram: \'93Please now! Jehovah has prevented me from bearing children. Please, have relations with my servant. Perhaps I can have children by means of her.\'94 So Abram listened to what Sarai said. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0After Abram had lived for ten years in the land of Canaan, Abram\'92s wife Sarai took her Egyptian servant Hagar and gave her to her husband Abram as his wife. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0So he had relations with Hagar, and she became pregnant. When she realized that she was pregnant, she began to despise her mistress.\
\cf4 5\cf5 \'a0At this Sarai said to Abram: \'93The injury done to me is your fault. I was the one who put my servant in your arms, but when she realized that she was pregnant, she began to despise me. May Jehovah judge between me and you.\'94 \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0So Abram said to Sarai: \'93Look! Your servant is under your authority. Do to her whatever you think is best.\'94 Then Sarai humiliated her, and she ran away from her.\
\cf4 7\cf5 \'a0Later Jehovah\'92s angel found her at a spring of waters in the wilderness, the spring on the way to Shur. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0And he said: \'93Hagar, servant of Sarai, where have you come from and where are you going?\'94 To this she said: \'93I am running away from my mistress Sarai.\'94 \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0Jehovah\'92s angel then said to her: \'93Return to your mistress and humble yourself under her hand.\'94 \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0Then Jehovah\'92s angel said: \'93I will greatly multiply your offspring, so that they will be too numerous to count.\'94 \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Jehovah\'92s angel added: \'93Here you are pregnant, and you will give birth to a son, and you must name him Ishmael, for Jehovah has heard your affliction. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0He will be a wild donkey of a man. His hand will be against everyone, and everyone\'92s hand will be against him, and he will dwell opposite all his brothers.\'94\
\cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Then she called on the name of Jehovah, who was speaking to her: \'93You are a God of sight,\'94 for she said: \'93Have I here actually looked upon the one who sees me?\'94 \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0That is why the well was called Beer-lahai-roi. (It is between Kadesh and Bered.) \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0So Hagar bore to Abram a son, and Abram named his son, whom Hagar bore, Ishmael. \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Abram was 86 years old when Hagar bore Ishmael to him.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

