\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0When Abram was 99 years old, Jehovah appeared to Abram and said to him: \'93I am God Almighty. Walk before me and prove yourself faultless. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0I will establish my covenant between me and you, and I will multiply you very, very much.\'94\
\cf4 3\cf5 \'a0At this Abram fell facedown, and God continued to speak with him, saying: \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0\'93As for me, look! my covenant is with you, and you will certainly become a father of many nations. \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0Your name will no longer be Abram; your name will become Abraham, for I will make you a father of many nations. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0I will make you very, very fruitful and will make you become nations, and kings will come from you.\
\cf4 7\cf5 \'a0\'93And I will keep my covenant between me and you and your offspring after you throughout their generations for an everlasting covenant, to be God to you and to your offspring after you. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0And I will give to you and to your offspring after you the land in which you lived as a foreigner\'97the entire land of Canaan\'97for a lasting possession, and I will be their God.\'94\
\cf4 9\cf5 \'a0God said further to Abraham: \'93As for you, you are to keep my covenant, you and your offspring after you throughout their generations. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0This is my covenant between me and you, that you and your offspring after you will keep: Every male among you must get circumcised. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0You must circumcise the flesh of your foreskins, and it will serve as a sign of the covenant between me and you. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Throughout your generations, every male among you eight days old must be circumcised, anyone who is born in the house and anyone who is not one of your offspring and who was purchased with money from a foreigner. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Every man born in your house and every man purchased with your money must be circumcised, and my covenant in your flesh must serve as a lasting covenant. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0If any uncircumcised male will not circumcise the flesh of his foreskin, that person must be cut off from his people. He has broken my covenant.\'94\
\cf4 15\cf5 \'a0Then God said to Abraham: \'93As for your wife Sarai, you must not call her Sarai, because Sarah will become her name. \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0I will bless her and also give you a son by her; I will bless her and she will become nations; kings of peoples will come from her.\'94 \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0At this Abraham fell facedown and began to laugh and to say in his heart: \'93Will a man 100 years old have a child born to him, and will Sarah, a woman 90 years old, give birth?\'94\
\cf4 18\cf5 \'a0So Abraham said to the true God: \'93O that Ishmael might live before you!\'94 \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0To this God said: \'93Your wife Sarah will definitely bear you a son, and you must name him Isaac. And I will establish my covenant with him for an everlasting covenant to his offspring after him. \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0But as regards Ishmael, I have heard you. Look! I will bless him and will make him fruitful and will multiply him very, very much. He will produce 12 chieftains, and I will make him become a great nation. \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0However, I will establish my covenant with Isaac, whom Sarah will bear to you at this appointed time next year.\'94\
\cf4 22\cf5 \'a0When God finished speaking with him, he went up from Abraham. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0Abraham then took Ishmael his son and all the men born in his house and everyone he had purchased with money, every male in the household of Abraham, and he circumcised the flesh of their foreskins on that very day, just as God had spoken with him. \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0Abraham was 99 years old when he had the flesh of his foreskin circumcised. \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0And Ishmael his son was 13 years old when he had the flesh of his foreskin circumcised. \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0On that very day, Abraham was circumcised and also his son Ishmael. \cf4 27\cf5 \'a0All the men of his household, anyone born in the house and anyone purchased with money from a foreigner, were also circumcised with him.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

