\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Afterward, Jehovah appeared to him among the big trees of Mamre while he was sitting at the entrance of the tent during the hottest part of the day. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0He looked up and saw three men standing some distance from him. When he saw them, he ran from the entrance of the tent to meet them, and he bowed down to the ground. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0Then he said: \'93Jehovah, if I have found favor in your eyes, please do not pass by your servant. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0Please, let a little water be brought and have your feet washed; then recline under the tree. \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0Seeing that you have come here to your servant, let me bring a piece of bread so that you may refresh yourselves. Then you may go on your way.\'94 At this they said: \'93All right. You may do as you have spoken.\'94\
\cf4 6\cf5 \'a0So Abraham hurried to the tent to Sarah and said: \'93Quick! Get three measures of fine flour, knead the dough, and make loaves of bread.\'94 \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0Next Abraham ran to the herd and chose a tender and good young bull. He gave it to the attendant, who hurried to prepare it. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0He then took butter and milk and the young bull that he had prepared and set the food before them. Then he stood by them under the tree as they were eating.\
\cf4 9\cf5 \'a0They said to him: \'93Where is your wife Sarah?\'94 He replied: \'93Here in the tent.\'94 \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0So one of them continued: \'93I will surely return to you next year at this time, and look! your wife Sarah will have a son.\'94 Now Sarah was listening at the tent entrance, which was behind the man. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Abraham and Sarah were old, being advanced in years. Sarah was past the age of childbearing. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0So Sarah began to laugh to herself, saying: \'93After I am worn out and my lord is old, will I really have this pleasure?\'94 \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Then Jehovah said to Abraham: \'93Why did Sarah laugh and say, \'91Am I really going to give birth even though I am old?\'92 \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0Is anything too extraordinary for Jehovah? I will return to you next year at this appointed time, and Sarah will have a son.\'94 \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0But Sarah denied it, saying, \'93I did not laugh!\'94 for she was afraid. At this he said: \'93Yes! You did laugh.\'94\
\cf4 16\cf5 \'a0When the men got up to leave and looked down toward Sodom, Abraham was walking with them to escort them. \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0Jehovah said: \'93Am I keeping hidden from Abraham what I am going to do? \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Why, Abraham is surely going to become a great and mighty nation, and all the nations of the earth will be blessed by means of him. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0For I have come to know him in order that he may command his sons and his household after him to keep Jehovah\'92s way by doing what is right and just, so that Jehovah may bring about what he has promised concerning Abraham.\'94\
\cf4 20\cf5 \'a0Then Jehovah said: \'93The outcry against Sodom and Gomorrah is indeed great, and their sin is very heavy. \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0I will go down to see whether they are acting according to the outcry that has reached me. And if not, I can get to know it.\'94\
\cf4 22\cf5 \'a0Then the men left from there and went toward Sodom, but Jehovah remained with Abraham. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0Then Abraham approached and said: \'93Will you really sweep away the righteous with the wicked? \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0Suppose there are 50 righteous men within the city. Will you, then, sweep them away and not pardon the place for the sake of the 50 righteous who are inside it? \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0It is unthinkable that you would act in this manner by putting the righteous man to death with the wicked one so that the outcome for the righteous man and the wicked is the same! It is unthinkable of you. Will the Judge of all the earth not do what is right?\'94 \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0Then Jehovah said: \'93If I find in Sodom 50 righteous men in the city, I will pardon the whole place for their sake.\'94 \cf4 27\cf5 \'a0But Abraham again responded: \'93Please, here I have presumed to speak to Jehovah, whereas I am dust and ashes. \cf4 28\cf5 \'a0Suppose the 50 righteous should lack five. Because of the five will you destroy the whole city?\'94 To this he said: \'93I will not destroy it if I find there 45.\'94\
\cf4 29\cf5 \'a0But yet again he spoke to him and said: \'93Suppose 40 are found there.\'94 He answered: \'93I will not do it for the sake of the 40.\'94 \cf4 30\cf5 \'a0But he continued: \'93Jehovah, please, do not become hot with anger, but let me go on speaking: Suppose only 30 are found there.\'94 He answered: \'93I will not do it if I find 30 there.\'94 \cf4 31\cf5 \'a0But he continued: \'93Please, here I have presumed to speak to Jehovah: Suppose only 20 are found there.\'94 He answered: \'93I will not destroy it for the sake of the 20.\'94 \cf4 32\cf5 \'a0Finally he said: \'93Jehovah, please, do not become hot with anger, but let me speak just once more: Suppose only ten are found there.\'94 He answered: \'93I will not destroy it for the sake of the ten.\'94 \cf4 33\cf5 \'a0When Jehovah finished speaking to Abraham, he went his way and Abraham returned to his place.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

