\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0The two angels arrived at Sodom by evening, and Lot was sitting in the gate of Sodom. When Lot saw them, he got up to meet them and bowed down with his face to the earth. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0And he said: \'93Please, my lords, turn aside, please, into the house of your servant and stay overnight and have your feet washed. Then you may get up early and travel on your way.\'94 To this they said: \'93No, we will stay overnight in the public square.\'94 \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0But he was so insistent with them that they went with him to his house. Then he made a feast for them, and he baked unleavened bread, and they ate.\
\cf4 4\cf5 \'a0Before they could lie down to sleep, the men of the city\'97the men of Sodom from boy to old man, all of them\'97surrounded the house in one mob. \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0And they kept calling out to Lot and saying to him: \'93Where are the men who came in to you tonight? Bring them out to us so that we may have sex with them.\'94\
\cf4 6\cf5 \'a0Then Lot went out to them to the doorway, and he shut the door behind him. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0He said: \'93Please, my brothers, do not act wickedly. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Please, here I have two daughters who have never had sexual relations with a man. Please, let me bring them out to you for you to do to them whatever seems good to you. But do not do anything to these men, for they have come under the shelter of my roof.\'94 \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0At this they said: \'93Stand back!\'94 And they added: \'93This lone foreigner came to live here, and yet he dares to judge us! Now we are going to do worse to you than to them.\'94 And they crowded in on Lot and moved forward to break down the door. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0So the men reached out their hands and brought Lot into the house with them, and they shut the door. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0But they struck the men who were at the entrance of the house with blindness, from the least to the greatest, so that they wore themselves out trying to find the doorway.\
\cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Then the men said to Lot: \'93Do you have anyone else here? Sons-in-law, your sons, your daughters, and all your people in the city, bring out of this place! \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0For we are going to destroy this place, because the outcry against them has indeed grown great before Jehovah, so that Jehovah sent us to destroy the city.\'94 \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0So Lot went out and began to speak to his sons-in-law who were to marry his daughters, and he kept saying: \'93Get up! Get out of this place, because Jehovah will destroy the city!\'94 But to his sons-in-law, he seemed to be joking.\
\cf4 15\cf5 \'a0As dawn was breaking, the angels became urgent with Lot, saying: \'93Get up! Take your wife and your two daughters who are here with you, so that you will not be swept away in the error of the city!\'94 \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0When he kept lingering, then because of Jehovah\'92s compassion for him, the men seized hold of his hand and the hand of his wife and the hands of his two daughters, and they brought him out and stationed him outside the city. \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0As soon as they had brought them to the outskirts, he said: \'93Escape for your life! Do not look behind you and do not stand still in any part of the district! Escape to the mountainous region so that you may not be swept away!\'94\
\cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Then Lot said to them: \'93Not there, please, Jehovah! \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0Please, now, your servant has found favor in your eyes and you are showing great kindness to me by preserving me alive, but I am not able to flee to the mountainous region because I am afraid that disaster may overtake me and I will die. \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0Please, now, this town is nearby and I can flee there; it is only a small place. May I, please, escape there? It is only a small place. Then I will survive.\'94 \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0So he said to him: \'93Very well, I will also show you consideration by not overthrowing the town you speak of. \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0Hurry! Escape there, because I cannot do anything until you arrive there!\'94 That is why he named the town Zoar.\
\cf4 23\cf5 \'a0The sun had risen over the land when Lot arrived at Zoar. \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0Then Jehovah made it rain sulfur and fire on Sodom and Gomorrah\'97it came from Jehovah, from the heavens. \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0So he overthrew these cities, yes, the entire district, including all the inhabitants of the cities and the plants of the ground. \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0But Lot\'92s wife, who was behind him, began to look back, and she became a pillar of salt.\
\cf4 27\cf5 \'a0Now Abraham got up early in the morning and went to the place where he had stood before Jehovah. \cf4 28\cf5 \'a0When he looked down toward Sodom and Gomorrah and all the land of the district, he saw quite a sight. There was dense smoke rising from the land like the dense smoke of a kiln! \cf4 29\cf5 \'a0So when God destroyed the cities of the district, God kept Abraham in mind by sending Lot out from the cities he overthrew, the cities where Lot had been dwelling.\
\cf4 30\cf5 \'a0Later Lot went up from Zoar with his two daughters and began living in the mountainous region, because he was afraid to live in Zoar. So he began living in a cave with his two daughters. \cf4 31\cf5 \'a0And the firstborn said to the younger: \'93Our father is old, and there is not a man in the land to have relations with us according to the custom of the whole earth. \cf4 32\cf5 \'a0Come, let us give our father wine to drink, and let us lie down with him and preserve offspring from our father.\'94\
\cf4 33\cf5 \'a0So that night they kept giving their father wine to drink; then the firstborn went in and lay down with her father, but he did not know when she lay down and when she got up. \cf4 34\cf5 \'a0Then on the next day, the firstborn said to the younger: \'93Here I lay down with my father last night. Let us give him wine to drink tonight also. Then you go in and lie down with him, and let us preserve offspring from our father.\'94 \cf4 35\cf5 \'a0So that night also, they repeatedly gave their father wine to drink; then the younger went and lay down with him, but he did not know when she lay down and when she got up. \cf4 36\cf5 \'a0So both daughters of Lot became pregnant by their father. \cf4 37\cf5 \'a0The firstborn gave birth to a son and named him Moab. He is the father of the Moabites of today. \cf4 38\cf5 \'a0The younger also gave birth to a son, and she named him Ben-ammi. He is the father of the Ammonites of today.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

