\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Now Abraham moved his camp from there to the land of the Negeb and began dwelling between Kadesh and Shur. While he was residing at Gerar, \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Abraham repeated concerning his wife Sarah: \'93She is my sister.\'94 So Abimelech king of Gerar sent for Sarah and took her. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0Afterward, God came by night to Abimelech in a dream and said to him: \'93Here you are as good as dead because of the woman whom you have taken, since she is married and belongs to another man.\'94 \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0However, Abimelech had not gone near her. So he said: \'93Jehovah, will you kill a nation that is really innocent? \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0Did he not say to me, \'91She is my sister,\'92 and did she too not say, \'91He is my brother\'92? I did this with an honest heart and innocent hands.\'94 \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0Then the true God said to him in the dream: \'93I know that you did this with an honest heart, so I held you back from sinning against me. That is why I did not allow you to touch her. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0Now return the man\'92s wife, for he is a prophet, and he will make supplication for you and you will keep living. But if you are not returning her, know that you will surely die, you and all who are yours.\'94\
\cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Abimelech got up early in the morning and called all his servants and told them all these things, and they became very frightened. \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0Then Abimelech called Abraham and said to him: \'93What have you done to us? What sin have I committed against you that you would bring upon me and my kingdom such a great sin? What you have done to me was not right.\'94 \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0And Abimelech went on to say to Abraham: \'93What were your intentions when you did this thing?\'94 \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Abraham said: \'93It was because I said to myself, \'91Surely there is no fear of God in this place, and they will kill me because of my wife.\'92 \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0And besides, she really is my sister, the daughter of my father but not the daughter of my mother, and she became my wife. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0So when God caused me to wander from the house of my father, I said to her: \'91Let this be how you show loyal love to me: Everywhere we go, say of me, \'93He is my brother.\'94\'92\'94\
\cf4 14\cf5 \'a0Abimelech then took sheep and cattle and male and female servants and gave them to Abraham, and he returned his wife Sarah to him. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0Abimelech also said: \'93Here my land is available to you. Dwell wherever you please.\'94 \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0And to Sarah he said: \'93Here I give 1,000 pieces of silver to your brother. It is a sign of your innocence to all who are with you and before everybody, and you are cleared of reproach.\'94 \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0And Abraham began to make supplication to the true God, and God healed Abimelech and his wife and his slave girls, and they began having children; \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0for Jehovah had made all the women of the house of Abimelech barren because of Sarah, Abraham\'92s wife.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

