\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Jehovah turned his attention to Sarah just as he had said, and Jehovah did for Sarah what he had promised. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0So Sarah became pregnant and then bore a son to Abraham in his old age at the appointed time God had promised him. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0Abraham named his newborn son, whom Sarah bore to him, Isaac. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0And Abraham circumcised his son Isaac when he was eight days old, just as God had commanded him. \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0Abraham was 100 years old when his son Isaac was born to him. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0Then Sarah said: \'93God has brought me laughter; everybody hearing of it will laugh with me.\'94 \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0And she added: \'93Who would have said to Abraham, \'91Sarah will certainly nurse children\'92? Yet, I have given birth to a son for him in his old age.\'94\
\cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Now the child grew and was weaned, and Abraham prepared a big feast on the day that Isaac was weaned. \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0But Sarah kept noticing that the son of Hagar the Egyptian, whom she had borne to Abraham, was mocking Isaac. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0So she said to Abraham: \'93Drive out this slave girl and her son, for the son of this slave girl is not going to be an heir along with my son, with Isaac!\'94 \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0But what she said about his son was very displeasing to Abraham. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Then God said to Abraham: \'93Do not be displeased by what Sarah is saying to you about the boy and about your slave girl. Listen to her, for what will be called your offspring will be through Isaac. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0As for the son of the slave girl, I will also make a nation out of him, because he is your offspring.\'94\
\cf4 14\cf5 \'a0So Abraham got up early in the morning and took bread and a skin bottle of water and gave it to Hagar. He set these on her shoulder and then sent her away along with the boy. So she departed and wandered about in the wilderness of Beer-sheba. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0Finally the water in the skin bottle was used up, and she pushed the boy under one of the bushes. \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Then she went on and sat down by herself, about the distance of a bowshot away, because she said: \'93I do not want to watch the boy die.\'94 So she sat down at a distance and began to cry aloud and to weep.\
\cf4 17\cf5 \'a0At that God heard the voice of the boy, and God\'92s angel called to Hagar from the heavens and said to her: \'93What is the matter with you, Hagar? Do not be afraid, for God has heard the voice of the boy there where he is. \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Get up, lift the boy and take hold of him with your hand, for I will make him a great nation.\'94 \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0Then God opened her eyes and she saw a well of water, and she went and filled the skin bottle with water and gave the boy a drink. \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0And God was with the boy as he grew up. He lived in the wilderness and became an archer. \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0He took up dwelling in the wilderness of Paran, and his mother took a wife for him from the land of Egypt.\
\cf4 22\cf5 \'a0At that time Abimelech together with Phicol the chief of his army said to Abraham: \'93God is with you in everything you are doing. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0So now swear to me here by God that you will not deal falsely with me and with my offspring and with my descendants, and that you will deal with me and with the land where you have been residing with the same loyal love that I have shown you.\'94 \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0So Abraham said: \'93I swear to this.\'94\
\cf4 25\cf5 \'a0However, Abraham complained to Abimelech about the well of water that the servants of Abimelech had violently seized. \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0Abimelech replied: \'93I do not know who did this; you did not tell me about it, and I heard nothing about it until today.\'94 \cf4 27\cf5 \'a0At that Abraham took sheep and cattle and gave them to Abimelech, and the two of them made a covenant. \cf4 28\cf5 \'a0When Abraham set seven female lambs apart from the flock by themselves, \cf4 29\cf5 \'a0Abimelech said to Abraham: \'93Why have you set these seven female lambs here by themselves?\'94 \cf4 30\cf5 \'a0Then he said: \'93You are to accept the seven female lambs from my hand as a witness that I dug this well.\'94 \cf4 31\cf5 \'a0That is why he called that place Beer-sheba, because there both of them had taken an oath. \cf4 32\cf5 \'a0So they made a covenant at Beer-sheba, after which Abimelech got up together with Phicol the chief of his army, and they returned to the land of the Philistines. \cf4 33\cf5 \'a0After that he planted a tamarisk tree at Beer-sheba, and there he called on the name of Jehovah, the everlasting God. \cf4 34\cf5 \'a0And Abraham stayed in the land of the Philistines for a long time.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

