\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Now after this the true God put Abraham to the test, and he said to him: \'93Abraham!\'94 to which he replied: \'93Here I am!\'94 \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Then he said: \'93Take, please, your son, your only son whom you so love, Isaac, and travel to the land of Moriah and offer him up there as a burnt offering on one of the mountains that I will designate to you.\'94\
\cf4 3\cf5 \'a0So Abraham got up early in the morning and saddled his donkey and took two of his servants along with him and his son Isaac. He split the wood for the burnt offering, and then he rose and traveled to the place that the true God indicated to him. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0On the third day, Abraham looked up and saw the place from a distance. \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0Abraham now said to his servants: \'93You stay here with the donkey, but the boy and I will go over there and worship and return to you.\'94\
\cf4 6\cf5 \'a0So Abraham took the wood for the burnt offering and put it on his son Isaac. Then he took in his hands the fire and the knife, and the two of them walked on together. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0Then Isaac said to his father Abraham: \'93My father!\'94 He replied: \'93Yes, my son!\'94 So he continued: \'93Here are the fire and the wood, but where is the sheep for the burnt offering?\'94 \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0To this Abraham said: \'93God himself will provide the sheep for the burnt offering, my son.\'94 And both of them walked on together.\
\cf4 9\cf5 \'a0Finally they reached the place that the true God had indicated to him, and Abraham built an altar there and arranged the wood on it. He bound his son Isaac hand and foot and put him on the altar on top of the wood. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0Then Abraham reached out his hand and took the knife to kill his son. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0But Jehovah\'92s angel called to him from the heavens and said: \'93Abraham, Abraham!\'94 to which he answered: \'93Here I am!\'94 \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Then he said: \'93Do not harm the boy, and do not do anything at all to him, for now I do know that you are God-fearing because you have not withheld your son, your only one, from me.\'94 \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0At that Abraham looked up, and there just beyond him was a ram caught by its horns in a thicket. So Abraham went and took the ram and offered it up as a burnt offering in place of his son. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0And Abraham named that place Jehovah-jireh. This is why it is still said today: \'93In the mountain of Jehovah it will be provided.\'94\
\cf4 15\cf5 \'a0And Jehovah\'92s angel called to Abraham a second time from the heavens, \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0saying: \'93\'91By myself I swear,\'92 declares Jehovah, \'91that because you have done this and you have not withheld your son, your only one, \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0I will surely bless you and I will surely multiply your offspring like the stars of the heavens and like the grains of sand on the seashore, and your offspring will take possession of the gate of his enemies. \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0And by means of your offspring all nations of the earth will obtain a blessing for themselves because you have listened to my voice.\'92\'94\
\cf4 19\cf5 \'a0After that Abraham returned to his servants, and they got up and went back together to Beer-sheba; and Abraham continued to dwell at Beer-sheba.\
\cf4 20\cf5 \'a0After this it was reported to Abraham: \'93Here Milcah has also borne sons to Nahor your brother: \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0Uz his firstborn, Buz his brother, Kemuel the father of Aram, \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0Chesed, Hazo, Pildash, Jidlaph, and Bethuel.\'94 \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0Bethuel became the father of Rebekah. Milcah bore these eight to Nahor the brother of Abraham. \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0His concubine, whose name was Reumah, also bore sons: Tebah, Gaham, Tahash, and Maacah.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

