\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0And Sarah lived for 127 years; these were the years of Sarah\'92s life. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0So Sarah died in Kiriath-arba, that is, Hebron, in the land of Canaan, and Abraham began to mourn and to weep over Sarah. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0Then Abraham got up from before his dead wife and he said to the sons of Heth: \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0\'93I am a foreigner and settler among you. Give me a property to serve as a burial place in your midst so that I may remove my dead for burial.\'94 \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0At this the sons of Heth answered Abraham: \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0\'93Hear us, my lord. You are a chieftain of God among us. You may bury your dead in the choicest of our burial places. None of us will hold back his burial place from you to prevent you from burying your dead.\'94\
\cf4 7\cf5 \'a0So Abraham got up and bowed down to the people of the land, to the sons of Heth, \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0and said to them: \'93If you agree to let me remove my dead for burial, then listen to me and urge Ephron the son of Zohar \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0to sell me the cave of Machpelah, which belongs to him; it is at the edge of his field. Let him sell it to me in your presence for the full amount of silver so that I may have a property for a burial place.\'94\
\cf4 10\cf5 \'a0Now Ephron was sitting among the sons of Heth. So Ephron the Hittite answered Abraham in the hearing of the sons of Heth, and before all who entered the gate of his city, saying: \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0\'93No, my lord! Listen to me. I give you both the field and the cave that is in it. In the presence of the sons of my people, I give it to you. Bury your dead.\'94 \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0At that Abraham bowed down before the people of the land \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0and spoke to Ephron in the hearing of the people, saying: \'93Listen to me, if you will! I will give you the full amount of silver for the field. Take it from me, in order that I may bury my dead there.\'94\
\cf4 14\cf5 \'a0Then Ephron answered Abraham: \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0\'93My lord, listen to me. This land is worth 400 silver shekels, but what is that between me and you? So bury your dead.\'94 \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Abraham listened to Ephron, and Abraham weighed out to Ephron the amount of silver that he had mentioned in the hearing of the sons of Heth, 400 silver shekels according to the weight accepted by the merchants. \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0Thus the field of Ephron in Machpelah, which was in front of Mamre\'97the field and the cave in it and all the trees within the boundaries of the field\'97became confirmed as \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Abraham\'92s purchased property in the presence of the sons of Heth, before all those entering the gate of his city. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0After that Abraham buried his wife Sarah in the cave of the field of Machpelah in front of Mamre, that is, Hebron, in the land of Canaan. \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0Thus the field and the cave that was in it were transferred by the sons of Heth to Abraham as property for a burial place.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

