\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Abraham was now old, advanced in years, and Jehovah had blessed Abraham in everything. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Abraham said to his servant, the oldest one of his household, who was managing all he had: \'93Please put your hand under my thigh, \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0and I will make you swear by Jehovah, the God of the heavens and the God of the earth, that you will not take a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, among whom I am dwelling. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0You must go instead to my country and to my relatives and take a wife for my son, for Isaac.\'94\
\cf4 5\cf5 \'a0However, the servant said to him: \'93What if the woman is not willing to come with me to this land? Must I then return your son to the land from which you came?\'94 \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0At this Abraham said to him: \'93See that you do not take my son there. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0Jehovah the God of the heavens, who took me from my father\'92s house and from the land of my relatives and who spoke with me and swore to me: \'91To your offspring I am going to give this land,\'92 he will send his angel ahead of you, and you will certainly take a wife for my son from there. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0But if the woman is unwilling to come with you, you will be free from this oath. But you must not take my son there.\'94 \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0With that the servant put his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master and swore to him concerning this matter.\
\cf4 10\cf5 \'a0So the servant took ten of his master\'92s camels and departed, taking along all sorts of good things from his master. Then he went on his way to Mesopotamia, to the city of Nahor. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0He had the camels kneel down at a well of water outside the city. It was about evening, the time when the women would go out to draw water. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Then he said: \'93Jehovah the God of my master Abraham, please grant me success this day, and show your loyal love to my master Abraham. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Here I am standing at a spring of water, and the daughters of the men of the city are coming out to draw water. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0May it happen that the young woman to whom I say, \'91Please let down your water jar so that I may take a drink,\'92 and who replies, \'91Take a drink, and I will also water your camels,\'92 let this be the one you choose for your servant Isaac; and by this let me know that you have shown your loyal love to my master.\'94\
\cf4 15\cf5 \'a0Even before he finished speaking, Rebekah, who was the daughter of Bethuel the son of Milcah the wife of Nahor, Abraham\'92s brother, came out with her water jar on her shoulder. \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Now the young woman was very beautiful, a virgin; no man had had sexual relations with her. She went down to the spring, filled her water jar, and then came back up. \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0At once the servant ran to meet her and said: \'93Please give me a little sip of water from your jar.\'94 \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0In turn she said: \'93Drink, my lord.\'94 With that she quickly lowered her jar upon her hand and gave him a drink. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0When she finished giving him a drink, she said: \'93I will also draw water for your camels until they are done drinking.\'94 \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0So she quickly emptied her jar into the drinking trough and ran again and again to the well to draw water, and she kept drawing water for all his camels. \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0The whole time the man silently stared at her in amazement, wondering whether Jehovah had made his trip successful or not.\
\cf4 22\cf5 \'a0When the camels had finished drinking, the man took out for her a gold nose ring weighing a half shekel and two bracelets of gold weighing ten shekels, \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0and he said: \'93Please tell me, whose daughter are you? Is there any room at your father\'92s house for us to spend the night?\'94 \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0At that she said to him: \'93I am the daughter of Bethuel the son of Milcah, whom she bore to Nahor.\'94 \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0And she added: \'93We have both straw and much fodder and also a place to spend the night.\'94 \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0Then the man bowed down and prostrated himself before Jehovah \cf4 27\cf5 \'a0and said: \'93May Jehovah be praised, the God of my master Abraham, for he has not abandoned his loyal love and his faithfulness toward my master. Jehovah has guided me to the house of the brothers of my master.\'94\
\cf4 28\cf5 \'a0And the young woman ran to tell her mother\'92s household about these things. \cf4 29\cf5 \'a0Now Rebekah had a brother whose name was Laban. So Laban ran to the man who was outside at the spring. \cf4 30\cf5 \'a0When he saw the nose ring and the bracelets on the hands of his sister and heard the words of his sister Rebekah, who was saying, \'93This is the way the man spoke to me,\'94 he came to meet the man, who was still there standing by the camels at the spring. \cf4 31\cf5 \'a0At once he said: \'93Come, you who are blessed by Jehovah. Why do you keep standing out here? I have made the house ready and a place for the camels.\'94 \cf4 32\cf5 \'a0With that the man came into the house, and he unharnessed the camels and gave straw and fodder to the camels and water to wash his feet and the feet of the men who were with him. \cf4 33\cf5 \'a0However, when something to eat was set before him, he said: \'93I will not eat until I have told you what I have to say.\'94 So Laban said: \'93Speak!\'94\
\cf4 34\cf5 \'a0Then he said: \'93I am Abraham\'92s servant. \cf4 35\cf5 \'a0And Jehovah has blessed my master very much, and he has made him very wealthy by giving him sheep and cattle, silver and gold, male and female servants, and camels and donkeys. \cf4 36\cf5 \'a0Further, Sarah the wife of my master bore a son to my master after she grew old, and he will give him everything he has. \cf4 37\cf5 \'a0So my master made me swear, saying: \'91You must not take a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose land I am dwelling. \cf4 38\cf5 \'a0No, but you will go to the house of my father and to my family, and you must take a wife for my son.\'92 \cf4 39\cf5 \'a0But I said to my master: \'91What if the woman is unwilling to come with me?\'92 \cf4 40\cf5 \'a0He said to me: \'91Jehovah, before whom I have walked, will send his angel with you and will certainly give success to your journey, and you must take a wife for my son from my family and from the house of my father. \cf4 41\cf5 \'a0You will be released from your oath to me if you go to my family and they will not give her to you. This will release you from your oath.\'92\
\cf4 42\cf5 \'a0\'93When I got to the spring today, I said: \'91Jehovah the God of my master Abraham, if you will make my journey successful, \cf4 43\cf5 \'a0here I am standing at a spring. What must take place is that when a young woman comes out to draw water, I will say, \'93Please, let me drink a little water from your jar,\'94 \cf4 44\cf5 \'a0and she will say to me, \'93You take a drink, and I will also draw water for your camels.\'94 Let that woman be the one whom Jehovah has chosen for the son of my master.\'92\
\cf4 45\cf5 \'a0\'93Before I was finished speaking in my heart, there was Rebekah coming out with her jar on her shoulder, and she made her way down to the spring and began to draw water. Then I said to her: \'91Give me a drink, please.\'92 \cf4 46\cf5 \'a0So she quickly lowered her jar from her shoulder and said: \'91Take a drink, and I will also water your camels.\'92 Then I took a drink, and she also watered the camels. \cf4 47\cf5 \'a0After that I asked her, \'91Whose daughter are you?\'92 to which she replied, \'91The daughter of Bethuel the son of Nahor, whom Milcah bore to him.\'92 So I put the ring on her nose and the bracelets on her hands. \cf4 48\cf5 \'a0And I bowed down and prostrated myself before Jehovah and praised Jehovah the God of my master Abraham, who had led me on the right path to take the daughter of the brother of my master for his son. \cf4 49\cf5 \'a0And now tell me if you wish to show loyal love and faithfulness toward my master; but if not, tell me, so that I may proceed one way or the other.\'94\
\cf4 50\cf5 \'a0Then Laban and Bethuel answered: \'93This is from Jehovah. We are not able to say yes or no to you. \cf4 51\cf5 \'a0Here is Rebekah before you. Take her and go, and let her become a wife to the son of your master, just as Jehovah has spoken.\'94 \cf4 52\cf5 \'a0When Abraham\'92s servant heard their words, he at once bowed down on the ground before Jehovah. \cf4 53\cf5 \'a0And the servant began to bring out articles of silver and of gold and garments and to give them to Rebekah, and he gave valuable things to her brother and to her mother. \cf4 54\cf5 \'a0After that he and the men with him ate and drank, and they spent the night there.\
When he got up in the morning, he said: \'93Send me off to my master.\'94 \cf4 55\cf5 \'a0To this her brother and her mother said: \'93Let the young woman stay with us at least ten days. Then she can go.\'94 \cf4 56\cf5 \'a0But he said to them: \'93Do not detain me, seeing that Jehovah has made my journey successful. Send me off, in order that I may go to my master.\'94 \cf4 57\cf5 \'a0So they said: \'93Let us call the young woman and inquire of her.\'94 \cf4 58\cf5 \'a0They called Rebekah and said to her: \'93Will you go with this man?\'94 She replied: \'93I am willing to go.\'94\
\cf4 59\cf5 \'a0So they sent off their sister Rebekah and her nurse and Abraham\'92s servant and his men. \cf4 60\cf5 \'a0And they blessed Rebekah and said to her: \'93Our sister, may you become thousands times ten thousand, and let your offspring take possession of the gate of those who hate them.\'94 \cf4 61\cf5 \'a0Then Rebekah and her female attendants rose, got on the camels, and followed the man. So the servant took Rebekah and went on his way.\
\cf4 62\cf5 \'a0Now Isaac had come from the direction of Beer-lahai-roi, for he was dwelling in the land of the Negeb. \cf4 63\cf5 \'a0And Isaac was out walking in the field about nightfall to meditate. When he looked up, why, he saw that camels were coming! \cf4 64\cf5 \'a0When Rebekah looked up, she caught sight of Isaac, and she quickly got down from the camel. \cf4 65\cf5 \'a0Then she asked the servant: \'93Who is that man there walking in the field to meet us?\'94 And the servant said: \'93It is my master.\'94 So she took her veil to cover herself. \cf4 66\cf5 \'a0And the servant told Isaac all the things he had done. \cf4 67\cf5 \'a0After that Isaac brought her into the tent of Sarah his mother. Thus he took Rebekah as his wife; and he fell in love with her, and Isaac found comfort after the loss of his mother.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

