\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0So Isaac called Jacob and blessed him and commanded him, saying: \'93You must not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Go away to Paddan-aram to the house of Bethuel, your mother\'92s father, and from there take for yourself a wife from the daughters of Laban, your mother\'92s brother. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0God Almighty will bless you and make you fruitful and multiply you, and you will certainly become a congregation of peoples. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0And he will give to you the blessing of Abraham, to you and to your offspring with you, so that you may take possession of the land where you have been living as a foreigner, which God has given to Abraham.\'94\
\cf4 5\cf5 \'a0So Isaac sent Jacob away, and he departed for Paddan-aram, to Laban the son of Bethuel the Aramaean, the brother of Rebekah, the mother of Jacob and Esau.\
\cf4 6\cf5 \'a0Esau saw that Isaac had blessed Jacob and had sent him away to Paddan-aram to take a wife from there and that when he blessed him, he commanded him, \'93Do not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan,\'94 \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0and that Jacob obeyed his father and his mother and departed for Paddan-aram. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Esau then realized that the daughters of Canaan were displeasing to his father Isaac, \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0so Esau went to Ishmael and took as wife Mahalath the daughter of Abraham\'92s son Ishmael, the sister of Nebaioth, in addition to the other wives he already had.\
\cf4 10\cf5 \'a0Jacob departed from Beer-sheba and kept going toward Haran. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0In time he came to a place and prepared to spend the night there because the sun had set. So he took one of the stones of that place and set it to rest his head on and lay down there. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Then he had a dream, and look! there was a stairway set on the earth, and its top reached up to the heavens; and there were God\'92s angels ascending and descending on it. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0And look! there was Jehovah stationed above it, and he said:\
\'93I am Jehovah the God of Abraham your father and the God of Isaac. The land on which you are lying, to you I am going to give it and to your offspring. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0And your offspring will certainly become like the dust particles of the earth, and you will spread abroad to the west and to the east and to the north and to the south, and by means of you and by means of your offspring all the families of the ground will certainly be blessed. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0I am with you, and I will safeguard you wherever you go, and I will return you to this land. I will not leave you until I have done what I have promised you.\'94\
\cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Then Jacob awoke from his sleep and said: \'93Truly Jehovah is in this place, and I did not know it.\'94 \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0And he grew fearful and added: \'93How awe-inspiring this place is! This can only be the house of God, and this is the gate of the heavens.\'94 \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0So Jacob got up early in the morning and took the stone on which he had rested his head and set it up as a pillar and poured oil on top of it. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0So he named that place Bethel, but previously the city\'92s name was Luz.\
\cf4 20\cf5 \'a0Jacob then made a vow, saying: \'93If God will continue with me and will protect me on my journey and will give me bread to eat and garments to wear \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0and I return in peace to the house of my father, then Jehovah will certainly have proved to be my God. \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0And this stone that I have set up as a pillar will become a house of God, and without fail I will give you a tenth of everything you give to me.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

