\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Now Jacob raised his eyes and saw Esau coming, and 400 men were with him. So he divided the children among Leah, Rachel, and the two female servants. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0He put the female servants and their children in front, Leah and her children after them, and Rachel and Joseph behind them. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0Then he himself went ahead of them and bowed down to the earth seven times as he came near to his brother.\
\cf4 4\cf5 \'a0But Esau ran to meet him, and he embraced him and kissed him, and they burst into tears. \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0When he raised his eyes and saw the women and the children, he said: \'93Who are these with you?\'94 to which he said: \'93The children with whom God has favored your servant.\'94 \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0At that the female servants came forward with their children and bowed down, \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0and Leah too came forward with her children, and they bowed down. Then Joseph came forward with Rachel, and they bowed down.\
\cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Esau said: \'93What is the purpose of all this camp of travelers that I have met?\'94 He replied: \'93In order to find favor in the eyes of my lord.\'94 \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0Then Esau said: \'93I have a great many possessions, my brother. Keep what is yours.\'94 \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0However, Jacob said: \'93No, please. If I have found favor in your eyes, you must take my gift from my hand, because I brought it so that I could see your face. And I have seen your face as though seeing God\'92s face, in that you received me with pleasure. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Take, please, the gift conveying my blessing that was brought to you, for God has favored me and I have everything I need.\'94 And he continued to urge him, so that he took it.\
\cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Later Esau said: \'93Let us move out and go, and let me go in advance of you.\'94 \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0But he said to him: \'93My lord is aware that the children are delicate and that in my care are sheep and cattle nursing their young. If they are driven too quickly for one day, then the whole flock will die. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0Let my lord, please, go on ahead of his servant, but I will continue the journey more slowly at the pace of my livestock and of the children until I come to my lord at Seir.\'94 \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0Then Esau said: \'93Please, let me leave some of my people with you.\'94 To this he said: \'93Why do this? Just let me find favor in the eyes of my lord.\'94 \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0So that day Esau went on his way back to Seir.\
\cf4 17\cf5 \'a0And Jacob journeyed to Succoth, and he built a house for himself and he made shelters for his herd. That was why he named the place Succoth.\
\cf4 18\cf5 \'a0After journeying from Paddan-aram, Jacob arrived safely at the city of Shechem in the land of Canaan, and he set up his camp near the city. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0Then he acquired a portion of the field where he pitched his tent from the sons of Hamor, the father of Shechem, for 100 pieces of money. \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0There he set up an altar and called it God, the God of Israel.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

