\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Now Dinah, Jacob\'92s daughter by Leah, used to go out to spend time with the young women of the land. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0When Shechem, the son of Hamor the Hivite, a chieftain of the land, saw her, he took her and lay down with her and violated her. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0And he became very attached to Dinah, the daughter of Jacob, and he fell in love with the young woman and spoke persuasively to her. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0Finally Shechem said to Hamor his father: \'93Get me this young woman to be my wife.\'94\
\cf4 5\cf5 \'a0When Jacob heard that he had defiled Dinah his daughter, his sons were with his herd in the field. So Jacob kept silent until they returned. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0Later Hamor, Shechem\'92s father, went out to speak with Jacob. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0But the sons of Jacob heard about it and returned from the field right away. They were offended and very angry because he had disgraced Israel by lying down with Jacob\'92s daughter, something that should not be done.\
\cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Hamor spoke with them, saying: \'93My son Shechem longs for your daughter. Please give her to him as his wife, \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0and form marriage alliances with us. Give us your daughters, and take our daughters for yourselves. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0You may dwell with us, and the land will become available for you. Dwell and carry on trade in it and settle in it.\'94 \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Then Shechem said to her father and to her brothers: \'93Let me find favor in your eyes, and I will give you whatever you ask me. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0You can demand from me a very high bride price and gift. I am willing to give whatever you may say to me. Just give me the young woman as a wife.\'94\
\cf4 13\cf5 \'a0And Jacob\'92s sons answered Shechem and Hamor his father deceitfully because he had defiled Dinah their sister. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0They said to them: \'93We cannot possibly do such a thing, to give our sister to a man who is not circumcised, for that is a disgrace to us. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0We can only consent on this condition: that you become like us and circumcise all your males. \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Then we will give our daughters to you, and we will take your daughters for ourselves, and we will dwell with you and become one people. \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0But if you do not listen to us and get circumcised, then we will take our daughter and go.\'94\
\cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Their words pleased Hamor and Shechem, Hamor\'92s son. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0The young man did not delay in doing what they asked, because he found delight in Jacob\'92s daughter, and he was the most honorable of the whole house of his father.\
\cf4 20\cf5 \'a0So Hamor and his son Shechem went to the city gate and spoke to the men of their city, saying: \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0\'93These men wish to be at peace with us. Let them dwell in the land and carry on trade in it, for the land is large enough to accommodate them. We can take their daughters as wives, and our daughters we can give to them. \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0Only on this one condition will the men consent to dwell with us in order to become one people: that every male among us be circumcised just the way they are circumcised. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0Then, will not their possessions, their wealth, and all their livestock be ours? So let us give them our consent that they may dwell with us.\'94 \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0All those going out by the gate of his city listened to Hamor and to his son Shechem, and all the males got circumcised, all those going out of the city gate.\
\cf4 25\cf5 \'a0However, on the third day, when they were still in pain, two sons of Jacob, Simeon and Levi, Dinah\'92s brothers, each took his sword and went into the unsuspecting city and killed every male. \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0They killed Hamor and his son Shechem with the sword and then took Dinah from Shechem\'92s house and left. \cf4 27\cf5 \'a0Jacob\'92s other sons came upon the slain men and plundered the city because they had defiled their sister. \cf4 28\cf5 \'a0They took their flocks, their herds, their donkeys, and whatever was in the city and in the field. \cf4 29\cf5 \'a0They also took all their possessions, captured all their little children and their wives, and plundered everything in the houses.\
\cf4 30\cf5 \'a0At this Jacob said to Simeon and to Levi: \'93You have brought great trouble on me in making me a stench to the inhabitants of the land, to the Canaanites and the Perizzites. I am few in number, and they will certainly gather together to attack me and I will be annihilated, I and my house.\'94 \cf4 31\cf5 \'a0But they said: \'93Should anyone treat our sister like a prostitute?\'94\
