\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0After that God said to Jacob: \'93Rise, go up to Bethel and dwell there, and make an altar there to the true God, who appeared to you when you were running away from Esau your brother.\'94\
\cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Then Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him: \'93Get rid of the foreign gods that are in your midst, and cleanse yourselves and change your garments, \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0and let us rise and go up to Bethel. There I will make an altar to the true God, who answered me in the day of my distress and who has been with me wherever I have gone.\'94 \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0So they gave Jacob all the foreign gods they had and the earrings that were in their ears, and Jacob buried them under the big tree that was close to Shechem.\
\cf4 5\cf5 \'a0When they traveled on, the terror of God struck the cities around them, so they did not chase after the sons of Jacob. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0Jacob eventually came to Luz, that is, Bethel, in the land of Canaan, he and all the people with him. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0There he built an altar and called the place El-bethel, because there the true God had revealed himself to him when he had run away from his brother. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Later Deborah, Rebekah\'92s nurse, died and was buried at the foot of Bethel under an oak. So he named it Allon-bacuth.\
\cf4 9\cf5 \'a0God appeared to Jacob once again while he was coming from Paddan-aram and blessed him. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0God said to him: \'93Your name is Jacob. Your name will no longer be Jacob, but Israel will be your name.\'94 And he began to call him Israel. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0God further said to him: \'93I am God Almighty. Be fruitful and become many. Nations and a congregation of nations will come from you, and kings will descend from you. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0As for the land that I have given to Abraham and to Isaac, to you I will give it, and to your offspring after you I will give the land.\'94 \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Then God went up from him at the place where he had spoken with him.\
\cf4 14\cf5 \'a0So Jacob set up a pillar in the place where he had spoken with him, a pillar of stone, and he poured a drink offering on it and poured oil on it. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0And Jacob continued to call the place where God had spoken with him Bethel.\
\cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Then they pulled away from Bethel. And while they were still some distance from Ephrath, Rachel began to give birth, and her labor was very difficult. \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0But while she was struggling to deliver the child, the midwife said to her: \'93Do not be afraid, for you will have this son also.\'94 \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Just as her life was slipping away (for she was dying), she named him Ben-oni, but his father called him Benjamin. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0So Rachel died and was buried on the way to Ephrath, that is, Bethlehem. \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0Jacob set up a pillar over her grave; it is the pillar of Rachel\'92s grave to this day.\
\cf4 21\cf5 \'a0After that Israel pulled away and pitched his tent a distance beyond the tower of Eder. \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0Once while Israel was dwelling in that land, Reuben went and lay down with Bilhah his father\'92s concubine, and Israel heard about it.\
So there were 12 sons of Jacob. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0The sons by Leah were Jacob\'92s firstborn Reuben, then Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun. \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0The sons by Rachel were Joseph and Benjamin. \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0And the sons by Bilhah, Rachel\'92s servant, were Dan and Naphtali. \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0And the sons by Zilpah, Leah\'92s servant, were Gad and Asher. These are Jacob\'92s sons, who were born to him in Paddan-aram.\
\cf4 27\cf5 \'a0Jacob eventually came to where his father Isaac was at Mamre, to Kiriath-arba, that is, Hebron, where Abraham and also Isaac had resided as foreigners. \cf4 28\cf5 \'a0Isaac lived to be 180 years old. \cf4 29\cf5 \'a0Then Isaac breathed his last and died and was gathered to his people, after a long and satisfying life; and his sons Esau and Jacob buried him.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

