\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0This is the history of Esau, that is, Edom.\
\cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Esau took his wives from the daughters of Canaan: Adah the daughter of Elon the Hittite; and Oholibamah the daughter of Anah, the granddaughter of Zibeon the Hivite; \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0and Basemath, Ishmael\'92s daughter, the sister of Nebaioth.\
\cf4 4\cf5 \'a0And Adah bore Eliphaz to Esau, and Basemath bore Reuel,\cf4  5\cf5 \'a0and Oholibamah bore Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.\
These are the sons of Esau, who were born to him in the land of Canaan. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0After that Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, all the members of his household, his herd and all his other beasts, and all the wealth he had accumulated in the land of Canaan and he went to another land some distance away from Jacob his brother. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0For their goods had become too many for them to dwell together, and the land where they were residing was not able to sustain them because of their herds. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0So Esau took up dwelling in the mountainous region of Seir. Esau is Edom.\
\cf4 9\cf5 \'a0And this is the history of Esau the father of Edom in the mountainous region of Seir.\
\cf4 10\cf5 \'a0These are the names of the sons of Esau: Eliphaz the son of Adah, Esau\'92s wife; Reuel the son of Basemath, Esau\'92s wife.\
\cf4 11\cf5 \'a0The sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Timna became the concubine of Eliphaz, Esau\'92s son. In time she bore to Eliphaz, Amalek. These are the sons of Adah, Esau\'92s wife.\
\cf4 13\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These were the sons of Basemath, Esau\'92s wife.\
\cf4 14\cf5 \'a0These were the sons of Oholibamah the daughter of Anah, the granddaughter of Zibeon, Esau\'92s wife, whom she bore to Esau: Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.\
\cf4 15\cf5 \'a0These are the sheikhs of the sons of Esau: The sons of Eliphaz, Esau\'92s firstborn: Sheikh Teman, Sheikh Omar, Sheikh Zepho, Sheikh Kenaz, \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Sheikh Korah, Sheikh Gatam, and Sheikh Amalek. These are the sheikhs of Eliphaz in the land of Edom. These are the sons by Adah.\
\cf4 17\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Reuel, Esau\'92s son: Sheikh Nahath, Sheikh Zerah, Sheikh Shammah, and Sheikh Mizzah. These are the sheikhs of Reuel in the land of Edom. These are the sons by Basemath, Esau\'92s wife.\
\cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Finally these are the sons of Oholibamah, Esau\'92s wife: Sheikh Jeush, Sheikh Jalam, and Sheikh Korah. These are the sheikhs of Oholibamah the daughter of Anah, Esau\'92s wife.\
\cf4 19\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Esau, and these are their sheikhs. He is Edom.\
\cf4 20\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Seir the Horite, the inhabitants of the land: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. These are the sheikhs of the Horites, the sons of Seir, in the land of Edom.\
\cf4 22\cf5 \'a0The sons of Lotan were Hori and Hemam, and Lotan\'92s sister was Timna.\
\cf4 23\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam.\
\cf4 24\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah. This is the Anah who found the hot springs in the wilderness while he was tending the donkeys for Zibeon his father.\
\cf4 25\cf5 \'a0These are the children of Anah: Dishon and Oholibamah the daughter of Anah.\
\cf4 26\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran.\
\cf4 27\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan.\
\cf4 28\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran.\
\cf4 29\cf5 \'a0These are the sheikhs of the Horites: Sheikh Lotan, Sheikh Shobal, Sheikh Zibeon, Sheikh Anah, \cf4 30\cf5 \'a0Sheikh Dishon, Sheikh Ezer, and Sheikh Dishan. These are the sheikhs of the Horites according to their sheikhs in the land of Seir.\
\cf4 31\cf5 \'a0Now these are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the Israelites. \cf4 32\cf5 \'a0Bela son of Beor reigned in Edom, and the name of his city was Dinhabah. \cf4 33\cf5 \'a0When Bela died, Jobab son of Zerah from Bozrah began to reign in his place. \cf4 34\cf5 \'a0When Jobab died, Husham from the land of the Temanites began to reign in his place. \cf4 35\cf5 \'a0When Husham died, Hadad son of Bedad, who defeated the Midianites in the territory of Moab, began to reign in his place, and the name of his city was Avith. \cf4 36\cf5 \'a0When Hadad died, Samlah from Masrekah began to reign in his place. \cf4 37\cf5 \'a0When Samlah died, Shaul from Rehoboth by the River began to reign in his place. \cf4 38\cf5 \'a0When Shaul died, Baal-hanan the son of Achbor began to reign in his place. \cf4 39\cf5 \'a0When Baal-hanan the son of Achbor died, Hadar began to reign in his place. The name of his city was Pau, and the name of his wife was Mehetabel the daughter of Matred the daughter of Mezahab.\
\cf4 40\cf5 \'a0So these are the names of the sheikhs of Esau according to their families, according to their places, by their names: Sheikh Timna, Sheikh Alvah, Sheikh Jetheth, \cf4 41\cf5 \'a0Sheikh Oholibamah, Sheikh Elah, Sheikh Pinon, \cf4 42\cf5 \'a0Sheikh Kenaz, Sheikh Teman, Sheikh Mibzar, \cf4 43\cf5 \'a0Sheikh Magdiel, and Sheikh Iram. These are the sheikhs of Edom according to their settlements in the land of their possession. This is Esau the father of Edom.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

