\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0About that time Judah left his brothers and pitched his tent near an Adullamite man named Hirah. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0There Judah saw the daughter of a certain Canaanite named Shua. So he took her and had relations with her, \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0and she became pregnant. Later she bore a son, and he named him Er. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0Again she became pregnant and bore a son and named him Onan. \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0Yet again she bore a son and named him Shelah. He was in Achzib when she bore him.\
\cf4 6\cf5 \'a0In time Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, and her name was Tamar. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0But Er, Judah\'92s firstborn, was displeasing to Jehovah; so Jehovah put him to death. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0In view of that, Judah said to Onan: \'93Have relations with your brother\'92s wife and perform brother-in-law marriage with her and raise up offspring for your brother.\'94 \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0But Onan knew that the offspring would not be considered his. So when he did have relations with his brother\'92s wife, he wasted his semen on the ground so as not to give offspring to his brother. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0What he did was bad in the eyes of Jehovah, so he also put him to death. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Judah said to Tamar his daughter-in-law: \'93Dwell as a widow in the house of your father until my son Shelah grows up,\'94 for he said to himself: \'91He too may die like his brothers.\'92 So Tamar went and stayed in her own father\'92s house.\
\cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Some time passed, and Judah\'92s wife, the daughter of Shua, died. Judah kept the mourning period, and then he went to his sheepshearers in Timnah with his companion Hirah the Adullamite. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Tamar was told: \'93Here your father-in-law is going up to Timnah to shear his sheep.\'94 \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0With that she removed her widow\'92s clothing and veiled herself and covered herself with a shawl and sat down at the entrance of Enaim, which is on the road to Timnah, for she saw that Shelah had grown up and yet she had not been given to him as a wife.\
\cf4 15\cf5 \'a0When Judah caught sight of her, he at once took her for a prostitute, because she had covered her face. \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0So he turned aside to her by the road and said: \'93Allow me, please, to have relations with you,\'94 for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law. However, she said: \'93What will you give me that you may have relations with me?\'94 \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0To this he said: \'93I will send a young goat from my herd.\'94 But she said: \'93Will you give a security until you send it?\'94 \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0He continued: \'93What security should I give you?\'94 to which she said: \'93Your seal ring and your cord and your rod that is in your hand.\'94 Then he gave them to her and had relations with her, and she became pregnant by him. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0After that she got up and went away and removed her shawl and clothed herself with her widow\'92s clothing.\
\cf4 20\cf5 \'a0And Judah sent the young goat by the hand of his companion the Adullamite, to get back the security from the hand of the woman, but he never found her. \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0He inquired of the men of her place, saying: \'93Where is that temple prostitute in Enaim along the road?\'94 But they said: \'93No temple prostitute has ever been in this place.\'94 \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0Finally he returned to Judah and said: \'93I never found her, and besides, the men of the place said, \'91No temple prostitute has ever been in this place.\'92\'94 \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0So Judah said: \'93Let her take them for herself, in order that we may not fall into contempt. At any rate, I have sent this young goat, but you never found her.\'94\
\cf4 24\cf5 \'a0However, about three months later, Judah was told: \'93Tamar your daughter-in-law has acted as a prostitute, and she is also pregnant by her prostitution.\'94 At that Judah said: \'93Bring her out and let her be burned.\'94 \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0As she was being brought out, she sent word to her father-in-law: \'93I am pregnant by the man to whom these belong.\'94 Then she added: \'93Please examine to whom these belong, the seal ring and the cord and the rod.\'94 \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0Then Judah examined them and said: \'93She is more righteous than I am, because I did not give her to Shelah my son.\'94 And he had no further sexual relations with her after that.\
\cf4 27\cf5 \'a0When the time came for her to give birth, there were twins in her womb. \cf4 28\cf5 \'a0As she was giving birth, one put out his hand, and the midwife immediately took a scarlet thread and tied it around his hand, saying: \'93This one came out first.\'94 \cf4 29\cf5 \'a0But as soon as he drew back his hand, his brother came out, and she exclaimed: \'93What a breach you have made for yourself!\'94 So he was named Perez. \cf4 30\cf5 \'a0Afterward his brother came out, around whose hand the scarlet thread was tied, and he was named Zerah.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

