\f1\b0 \cf3 45\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0At this Joseph could no longer control himself before all his attendants. So he cried out: \'93Have everyone leave me!\'94 No one else stayed with him while Joseph made himself known to his brothers.\
\cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Then he began to weep so loudly that the Egyptians heard it and Pharaoh\'92s house heard it. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0Finally Joseph said to his brothers: \'93I am Joseph. Is my father still alive?\'94 But his brothers were unable to answer him at all, because they were astonished on account of him. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0So Joseph said to his brothers: \'93Come close to me, please.\'94 With that they came close to him.\
Then he said: \'93I am Joseph your brother, whom you sold into Egypt. \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0But now do not be upset and do not reproach one another because you sold me here; because God has sent me ahead of you for the preservation of life. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0This is the second year of the famine in the land, and there are yet five years in which there will be no plowing or harvest. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0But God sent me ahead of you in order to preserve for you a remnant on the earth and to keep you alive by a great deliverance. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0So, then, it was not you who sent me here, but it was the true God, in order to appoint me as chief adviser to Pharaoh and lord for all his house and ruler over all the land of Egypt.\
\cf4 9\cf5 \'a0\'93Return quickly to my father, and you must say to him, \'91This is what your son Joseph has said: \'93God has appointed me lord over all Egypt. Come down to me. Do not delay. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0You must dwell in the land of Goshen, where you will be near me\'97you, your sons, your grandsons, your flocks, your herds, and everything you have. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0I will supply you with food there, for there are yet five years of famine. Otherwise, you and your house and everything you have will come to poverty.\'94\'92 \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0You and my brother Benjamin can now see with your own eyes that I am really the one speaking to you. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0So you must tell my father about all my glory in Egypt and everything you have seen. Now hurry and bring my father down here.\'94\
\cf4 14\cf5 \'a0Then he embraced his brother Benjamin and gave way to weeping, and Benjamin wept with his arms around his neck. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0And he kissed all his brothers and wept over them, and after that his brothers spoke with him.\
\cf4 16\cf5 \'a0The news reached the house of Pharaoh: \'93Joseph\'92s brothers have come!\'94 It was good in the eyes of Pharaoh and his servants. \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0So Pharaoh said to Joseph: \'93Tell your brothers, \'91Do this: Load your beasts of burden and go to the land of Canaan, \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0and take your father and your households and come here to me. I will give you the good things of the land of Egypt, and you will eat the richest part of the land.\'92 \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0And you are commanded to tell them: \'91Do this: Take wagons from the land of Egypt for your children and your wives, and you must bring your father on one of them and come here. \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0Do not worry about your belongings, for the best of all the land of Egypt is yours.\'92\'94\
\cf4 21\cf5 \'a0And the sons of Israel did so, and Joseph gave them wagons according to Pharaoh\'92s orders, and he gave them provisions for the journey. \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0To each of them he gave individual changes of clothing, but to Benjamin he gave 300 silver pieces and five changes of clothing. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0And to his father he sent the following: ten donkeys carrying good things of Egypt and ten female donkeys carrying grain and bread and sustenance for his father for the journey. \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0So he sent his brothers off, and as they departed, he said to them: \'93Do not become upset with one another on the way.\'94\
\cf4 25\cf5 \'a0Then they went up from Egypt and came into the land of Canaan to their father Jacob. \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0Then they reported to him: \'93Joseph is still alive, and he is the ruler over all the land of Egypt!\'94 But his heart grew numb because he did not believe them. \cf4 27\cf5 \'a0When they went on telling him all the words that Joseph had spoken to them and when he saw the wagons that Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of their father Jacob began to revive. \cf4 28\cf5 \'a0Israel exclaimed: \'93It is enough! My son Joseph is still alive! I must go and see him before I die!\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 Chapter 
\f1\b0 \cf3 46\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0So Israel took all that he had and departed. When he arrived at Beer-sheba, he offered sacrifices to the God of his father Isaac. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Then God spoke to Israel in a vision by night and said: \'93Jacob, Jacob!\'94 to which he said: \'93Here I am!\'94 \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0He said: \'93I am the true God, the God of your father. Do not be afraid to go down to Egypt, for there I will make you into a great nation. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0I myself will go down with you to Egypt, and I myself will also bring you back from there, and Joseph will lay his hand on your eyes.\'94\
\cf4 5\cf5 \'a0After that Jacob departed from Beer-sheba, and the sons of Israel transported Jacob their father and their children and their wives in the wagons that Pharaoh had sent to transport him. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0They took along their herds and their goods, which they had accumulated in the land of Canaan. And so they came into Egypt, Jacob and all his offspring with him. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0He brought with him into Egypt his sons and his grandsons, his daughters and his granddaughters\'97all his offspring.\
\cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Now these are the names of Israel\'92s sons who came into Egypt, Jacob and his sons: Jacob\'92s firstborn was Reuben.\
\cf4 9\cf5 \'a0The sons of Reuben were Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.\
\cf4 10\cf5 \'a0The sons of Simeon were Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul the son of a Canaanite woman.\
\cf4 11\cf5 \'a0The sons of Levi were Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.\
\cf4 12\cf5 \'a0The sons of Judah were Er, Onan, Shelah, Perez, and Zerah. However, Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan.\
The sons of Perez came to be Hezron and Hamul.\
\cf4 13\cf5 \'a0The sons of Issachar were Tola, Puvah, Iob, and Shimron.\
\cf4 14\cf5 \'a0The sons of Zebulun were Sered, Elon, and Jahleel.\
\cf4 15\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Leah, whom she bore to Jacob in Paddan-aram, together with his daughter Dinah. All his sons and his daughters numbered 33.\
\cf4 16\cf5 \'a0The sons of Gad were Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi, and Areli.\
\cf4 17\cf5 \'a0The sons of Asher were Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, and Beriah, and their sister was Serah.\
The sons of Beriah were Heber and Malchiel.\
\cf4 18\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Zilpah, whom Laban gave to his daughter Leah. She bore these to Jacob: 16 persons in all.\
\cf4 19\cf5 \'a0The sons of Jacob\'92s wife Rachel were Joseph and Benjamin.\
\cf4 20\cf5 \'a0There were born to Joseph in the land of Egypt Manasseh and Ephraim, whom Asenath the daughter of Potiphera the priest of On bore to him.\
\cf4 21\cf5 \'a0The sons of Benjamin were Bela, Becher, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi, Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, and Ard.\
\cf4 22\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Rachel who were born to Jacob: 14 persons in all.\
\cf4 23\cf5 \'a0The son of Dan was Hushim.\
\cf4 24\cf5 \'a0The sons of Naphtali were Jahzeel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem.\
\cf4 25\cf5 \'a0These are the sons of Bilhah, whom Laban gave to his daughter Rachel. She bore these to Jacob: seven persons in all.\
\cf4 26\cf5 \'a0All those who descended from Jacob and went into Egypt with him, aside from the wives of Jacob\'92s sons, were 66. \cf4 27\cf5 \'a0Joseph\'92s sons who were born to him in Egypt were two. All the people of the house of Jacob who came into Egypt were 70.\
\cf4 28\cf5 \'a0Jacob sent Judah ahead to tell Joseph that he was on the way to Goshen. When they came into the land of Goshen, \cf4 29\cf5 \'a0Joseph had his chariot prepared and went up to meet Israel his father at Goshen. When he presented himself to him, he at once embraced him and wept for some time. \cf4 30\cf5 \'a0Then Israel said to Joseph: \'93Now I am ready to die; I have seen your face and know that you are still alive.\'94\
\cf4 31\cf5 \'a0Joseph then said to his brothers and to his father\'92s household: \'93Let me go up and report to Pharaoh and tell him, \'91My brothers and my father\'92s household who were in the land of Canaan have come here to me. \cf4 32\cf5 \'a0The men are shepherds, and they raise livestock, and they have brought their flocks and their herds and all that they have.\'92 \cf4 33\cf5 \'a0When Pharaoh calls you and asks, \'91What is your occupation?\'92 \cf4 34\cf5 \'a0you must say, \'91Your servants have raised livestock from our youth until now, both we and our forefathers,\'92 so that you may dwell in the land of Goshen, for every herder of sheep is detestable to the Egyptians.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 Chapter 
\f1\b0 \cf3 47\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0So Joseph went and reported to Pharaoh: \'93My father and my brothers and their flocks and their herds and all that they possess have come from the land of Canaan, and they are in the land of Goshen.\'94 \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0He took five of his brothers and presented them to Pharaoh.\
\cf4 3\cf5 \'a0Pharaoh said to his brothers: \'93What is your occupation?\'94 They replied to Pharaoh: \'93Your servants are herders of sheep, both we and our forefathers.\'94 \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0Then they said to Pharaoh: \'93We have come to reside as foreigners in the land because there are no pastures for the flock of your servants, for the famine is severe in the land of Canaan. So please let your servants dwell in the land of Goshen.\'94 \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0At that Pharaoh said to Joseph: \'93Your father and your brothers have come here to you. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0The land of Egypt is at your disposal. Have your father and your brothers dwell in the very best part of the land. Let them dwell in the land of Goshen, and if you know of any capable men among them, put them in charge of my livestock.\'94\
\cf4 7\cf5 \'a0Then Joseph brought in Jacob his father and presented him to Pharaoh, and Jacob blessed Pharaoh. \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Pharaoh asked Jacob: \'93How old are you?\'94 \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0Jacob said to Pharaoh: \'93The years of my wanderings are 130. Few and distressing the years of my life have been, and they are not as long as the years of the lives of my forefathers during their wanderings.\'94 \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0After that Jacob blessed Pharaoh and went out from before him.\
\cf4 11\cf5 \'a0So Joseph settled his father and his brothers, and he gave them a possession in the land of Egypt, in the very best part of the land, in the land of Rameses, just as Pharaoh had commanded. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0And Joseph kept supplying his father and his brothers and the entire household of his father with food according to the number of their children.\
\cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Now there was no food in all the land, because the famine was very severe, and the land of Egypt and the land of Canaan became exhausted as a result of the famine. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0Joseph was collecting all the money that was to be found in the land of Egypt and in the land of Canaan for the grain that people were buying, and Joseph kept bringing the money into Pharaoh\'92s house. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0In time the money from the land of Egypt and the land of Canaan was spent, and all the Egyptians began coming to Joseph, saying: \'93Give us food! Why should we die before your very eyes because our money has run out?\'94 \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0Then Joseph said: \'93If your money has run out, hand over your livestock, and I will give you food in exchange for your livestock.\'94 \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0So they began bringing their livestock to Joseph, and Joseph kept giving them food in exchange for their horses, the livestock of the flock and of the herd, and the donkeys, and he kept providing them with food in exchange for all their livestock during that year.\
\cf4 18\cf5 \'a0When that year came to its close, they began coming to him the next year and saying: \'93We will not hide from my lord that the money and the stock of domestic animals have already been given to my lord. We have nothing left for my lord but our bodies and our land. \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0Why should we die before your eyes, both we and our land? Buy us and our land in exchange for food, and we together with our land will become slaves to Pharaoh. Give us seed so that we may live and not die and that our land may not become desolate.\'94 \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0Joseph then bought all the land of the Egyptians for Pharaoh because every Egyptian sold his field, for the famine was very severe; and the land became Pharaoh\'92s.\
\cf4 21\cf5 \'a0Then he moved the people into cities, from one end of the territory of Egypt to its other end. \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0Only the land of the priests he did not buy, because the rations for the priests were from Pharaoh and they lived on their rations that Pharaoh gave them. That is why they did not sell their land. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0Then Joseph said to the people: \'93See, I have today bought you and your land for Pharaoh. Here is seed for you, and you must sow the land with it. \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0When it produces, give a fifth to Pharaoh, but four parts will be yours as seed for the field and as food for you and for those in your houses and for your children to eat.\'94 \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0So they said: \'93You have preserved our lives. Let us find favor in the eyes of my lord, and we will become slaves to Pharaoh.\'94 \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0Then Joseph made it a decree, which is valid until today over the land of Egypt, that a fifth belongs to Pharaoh. It was only the land of the priests that did not become Pharaoh\'92s.\
\cf4 27\cf5 \'a0Israel continued to dwell in the land of Egypt, in the land of Goshen, and they settled in it and were fruitful and increased greatly. \cf4 28\cf5 \'a0And Jacob lived on in the land of Egypt for 17 years, so that the days of Jacob\'92s life came to be 147 years.\
\cf4 29\cf5 \'a0The time was approaching for Israel to die, so he called his son Joseph and said: \'93If, now, I have found favor in your eyes, place your hand, please, under my thigh, and show loyal love and faithfulness to me. Please, do not bury me in Egypt. \cf4 30\cf5 \'a0When I die, you must carry me out of Egypt and bury me in the grave of my forefathers.\'94 Accordingly, he said: \'93I will do just as you say.\'94 \cf4 31\cf5 \'a0Then he said: \'93Swear to me.\'94 So he swore to him. At that Israel bowed down at the head of his bed.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

