\f1\b0 \cf3 48\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0After these things, Joseph was told: \'93Look, your father is getting weak.\'94 At that he took his two sons Manasseh and Ephraim with him. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Then Jacob was told: \'93Here your son Joseph has come to you.\'94 So Israel gathered his strength and sat up on his bed. \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0And Jacob said to Joseph:\
\'93God Almighty appeared to me at Luz in the land of Canaan and blessed me. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0And he said to me, \'91I am making you fruitful, and I will make you many, and I will transform you into a congregation of peoples, and I will give this land to your offspring after you as a lasting possession.\'92 \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0Now your two sons who were born to you in the land of Egypt before I came to you in Egypt are mine. Ephraim and Manasseh will become mine just as Reuben and Simeon are mine. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0But the children born to you after them will become yours. They will be called by the name of their brothers in their inheritance. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0As for me, when I was coming from Paddan, Rachel died alongside me in the land of Canaan, while there was yet a good stretch of land before coming to Ephrath. So I buried her there on the way to Ephrath, that is, Bethlehem.\'94\
\cf4 8\cf5 \'a0Then Israel saw Joseph\'92s sons and asked: \'93Who are these?\'94 \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0So Joseph said to his father: \'93They are my sons whom God has given me in this place.\'94 At this he said: \'93Bring them to me, please, so that I may bless them.\'94 \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0Now the eyes of Israel were failing from age, and he was unable to see. So Joseph brought them close to him, and he kissed them and embraced them. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Israel said to Joseph: \'93I never imagined I would see your face, but here God has also let me see your offspring.\'94 \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Joseph then removed them from Israel\'92s knees, and he bowed down with his face to the ground.\
\cf4 13\cf5 \'a0Joseph now took the two of them, Ephraim with his right hand to Israel\'92s left and Manasseh with his left hand to Israel\'92s right, and brought them close to him. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0However, Israel put out his right hand and placed it on Ephraim\'92s head, although he was the younger, and he placed his left hand on Manasseh\'92s head. He purposely laid his hands this way, since Manasseh was the firstborn. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0Then he blessed Joseph and said:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li432\fi-432\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \'93The true God before whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac walked,\
The true God who has been shepherding me during all my life until this day,\
\pard\pardeftab720\li432\fi-432\partightenfactor0
\cf4 16\cf6 \'a0The angel who has been recovering me from all calamity, bless the boys.\
Let my name be called upon them and the name of my fathers, Abraham and Isaac,\
Let them increase to a multitude in the earth.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0
\cf4 17\cf5 \'a0When Joseph saw that his father kept his right hand placed on Ephraim\'92s head, it was displeasing to him, so he tried to take hold of his father\'92s hand to move it from Ephraim\'92s head to Manasseh\'92s head. \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Joseph said to his father: \'93Not so, my father, because this is the firstborn. Put your right hand on his head.\'94 \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0But his father kept refusing and said: \'93I know it, my son, I know it. He too will become a people, and he too will become great. Nevertheless, his younger brother will become greater than he will, and his offspring will become the full equivalent of nations.\'94 \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0So he continued to bless them on that day, saying:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li432\fi-432\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \'93Let Israel mention you when they pronounce blessings, saying,\
\'91May God make you like Ephraim and like Manasseh.\'92\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0
\cf5 Thus he kept putting Ephraim before Manasseh.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0
\cf4 21\cf5 \'a0Then Israel said to Joseph: \'93Look, I am dying, but God will certainly continue with you and return you to the land of your forefathers. \cf4 22\cf5 \'a0As for me, I do give you one portion of land more than to your brothers, which I took from the hand of the Amorites with my sword and my bow.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 Chapter 
\f1\b0 \cf3 49\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi576\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0And Jacob called his sons and said: \'93Gather yourselves together that I may tell you what will happen to you in the final part of the days. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0Assemble yourselves and listen, you sons of Jacob, yes, listen to Israel your father.\
\cf4 3\cf5 \'a0\'93Reuben, you are my firstborn, my vigor and the beginning of my procreative power, the excellence of dignity and the excellence of strength. \cf4 4\cf5 \'a0With recklessness like turbulent waters, you will not excel, because you have gone up to your father\'92s bed. At that time you defiled my bed. He actually went on to it!\
\cf4 5\cf5 \'a0\'93Simeon and Levi are brothers. Instruments of violence are their slaughter weapons. \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0Into their company do not come, O my soul. With their assembly do not join, O my honor, because in their anger they killed men, and for their pleasure they hamstrung bulls. \cf4 7\cf5 \'a0Cursed be their anger, because it is cruel, and their fury, because it is harsh. Let me disperse them in Jacob, and let me scatter them in Israel.\
\cf4 8\cf5 \'a0\'93As for you, Judah, your brothers will praise you. Your hand will be on the neck of your enemies. The sons of your father will bow down before you. \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0Judah is a lion cub. From the prey, my son, you will certainly go up. He has crouched down and stretched himself out like a lion, and like a lion, who dares rouse him? \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0The scepter will not depart from Judah, neither the commander\'92s staff from between his feet, until Shiloh comes, and to him the obedience of the peoples will belong. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0Tying his donkey to a vine and his donkey\'92s colt to a choice vine, he will wash his clothing in wine and his garment in the blood of grapes. \cf4 12\cf5 \'a0Dark red are his eyes from wine, and his teeth are white from milk.\
\cf4 13\cf5 \'a0\'93Zebulun will reside by the seashore, by the shore where the ships lie anchored, and his remote border will be toward Sidon.\
\cf4 14\cf5 \'a0\'93Issachar is a strong-boned donkey, lying down between the two saddlebags. \cf4 15\cf5 \'a0And he will see that the resting-place is good and that the land is pleasant. He will bend his shoulder to bear the burden and will submit to forced labor.\
\cf4 16\cf5 \'a0\'93Dan will judge his people as one of the tribes of Israel. \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0Let Dan be a serpent by the roadside, a horned snake beside the path, that bites the heels of the horse so that its rider falls backward. \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0I will wait for salvation from you, O Jehovah.\
\cf4 19\cf5 \'a0\'93As for Gad, a marauder band will raid him, but he will raid at their heels.\
\cf4 20\cf5 \'a0\'93Asher\'92s bread will be abundant, and he will provide food fit for a king.\
\cf4 21\cf5 \'a0\'93Naphtali is a slender doe. He is speaking words of elegance.\
\cf4 22\cf5 \'a0\'93Joseph is the offshoot of a fruitful tree, a fruitful tree by a spring, whose branches extend over the wall. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0But the archers kept harassing him and shot at him and kept harboring animosity against him. \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0And yet his bow remained in place, and his hands stayed strong and agile. This was from the hands of the powerful one of Jacob, from the shepherd, the stone of Israel. \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0He is from the God of your father, and he will help you, and he is with the Almighty, and he will bless you with the blessings of the heavens above, with the blessings of the deep below, with the blessings of the breasts and womb. \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0The blessings of your father will be superior to the blessings of the eternal mountains, to the desirable things of the enduring hills. They will continue upon the head of Joseph, upon the crown of the head of the one singled out from his brothers.\
\cf4 27\cf5 \'a0\'93Benjamin will keep on tearing like a wolf. In the morning he will eat the prey, and in the evening he will divide spoil.\'94\
\cf4 28\cf5 \'a0All of these are the 12 tribes of Israel, and this is what their father said to them when he was blessing them. He gave each of them an appropriate blessing.\
\cf4 29\cf5 \'a0After that he gave these commands to them: \'93I am being gathered to my people. Bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the Hittite, \cf4 30\cf5 \'a0the cave in the field of Machpelah in front of Mamre in the land of Canaan, the field that Abraham purchased from Ephron the Hittite as a property for a burial place. \cf4 31\cf5 \'a0There they buried Abraham and his wife Sarah. There they buried Isaac and his wife Rebekah, and there I buried Leah. \cf4 32\cf5 \'a0The field and the cave that is in it were purchased from the sons of Heth.\'94\
\cf4 33\cf5 \'a0Thus Jacob finished giving these instructions to his sons. Then he drew his feet up onto the bed and breathed his last and was gathered to his people.\
