\f2\fs24 \cf4 1\cf5 \'a0Joseph then threw himself on his father and wept over him and kissed him. \cf4 2\cf5 \'a0After that Joseph commanded his servants, the physicians, to embalm his father. So the physicians embalmed Israel, \cf4 3\cf5 \'a0and they took the full 40 days for him, for this is the full period for the embalming, and the Egyptians continued to shed tears for him 70 days.\
\cf4 4\cf5 \'a0When the days of mourning for him passed, Joseph spoke to Pharaoh\'92s court, saying: \'93If I have found favor in your eyes, give this message to Pharaoh: \cf4 5\cf5 \'a0\'91My father made me swear, saying: \'93Look! I am dying. You are to bury me in my burial place, which I have excavated in the land of Canaan.\'94 Please, let me go up and bury my father, after which I will return.\'92\'94 \cf4 6\cf5 \'a0Pharaoh replied: \'93Go and bury your father just as he made you swear.\'94\
\cf4 7\cf5 \'a0So Joseph went up to bury his father, and all of Pharaoh\'92s servants went with him, the elders of his court and all the elders of the land of Egypt \cf4 8\cf5 \'a0and all of Joseph\'92s household and his brothers and the household of his father. Only their little children and their flocks and their herds they left in the land of Goshen. \cf4 9\cf5 \'a0Chariots and horsemen also went up with him, and the camp was very numerous. \cf4 10\cf5 \'a0Then they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is in the region of the Jordan, and there they carried on a very great and bitter mourning, and he kept mourning for his father seven days. \cf4 11\cf5 \'a0The inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw them mourning at the threshing floor of Atad, and they exclaimed: \'93This is a great mourning for the Egyptians!\'94 That is why it was named Abel-mizraim, which is in the region of the Jordan.\
\cf4 12\cf5 \'a0So his sons did for him exactly as he had instructed them. \cf4 13\cf5 \'a0His sons carried him into the land of Canaan and buried him in the cave of the field of Machpelah, the field in front of Mamre that Abraham had purchased from Ephron the Hittite as property for a burial place. \cf4 14\cf5 \'a0After he buried his father, Joseph returned to Egypt with his brothers and all those who had gone with him to bury his father.\
\cf4 15\cf5 \'a0When Joseph\'92s brothers saw that their father was dead, they said: \'93It may be that Joseph is harboring animosity against us and that he will repay us for all the evil that we did to him.\'94 \cf4 16\cf5 \'a0So they sent a message to Joseph in these words: \'93Your father gave this command before his death: \cf4 17\cf5 \'a0\'91This is what you are to say to Joseph: \'93I beg you, please pardon the transgression of your brothers and the sin they committed in bringing such harm to you.\'94\'92 Now, please, pardon the transgression of the servants of your father\'92s God.\'94 And Joseph wept when they spoke to him. \cf4 18\cf5 \'a0Then his brothers also came and fell down before him and said: \'93Here we are as slaves to you!\'94 \cf4 19\cf5 \'a0Joseph said to them: \'93Do not be afraid. Am I in the place of God? \cf4 20\cf5 \'a0Although you meant to harm me, God intended it to turn out well and to preserve many people alive, as he is doing today. \cf4 21\cf5 \'a0So now do not be afraid. I will keep supplying you and your little children with food.\'94 Thus he comforted them and spoke reassuringly to them.\
\cf4 22\cf5 \'a0And Joseph continued to dwell in Egypt, he and the household of his father, and Joseph lived for 110 years. \cf4 23\cf5 \'a0Joseph saw the third generation of Ephraim\'92s sons, also the sons of Machir, Manasseh\'92s son. They were born upon Joseph\'92s knees. \cf4 24\cf5 \'a0At length Joseph said to his brothers: \'93I am dying, but God will without fail turn his attention to you, and he will certainly bring you up out of this land to the land about which he swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.\'94 \cf4 25\cf5 \'a0So Joseph made the sons of Israel swear, saying: \'93God will without fail turn his attention to you. You must take my bones up out of here.\'94 \cf4 26\cf5 \'a0And Joseph died at the age of 110, and they had him embalmed, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt. }